sentences: William Henry Joseph Bonaparte Bertholf Smith (November 23, 1893 – April 18, 1973), also known as "The Lion", was an American jazz and stride pianist.
William Henry Joseph Bonaparte Bertholf, known as Willie, was born in 1893 in Goshen, New York.

After Frank Bertholf died in 1901, his mother married John Smith, a master mechanic from Paterson, New Jersey.
John Smith worked for C.M. Bailey, Pork Packers, and he would leave the house around midnight to pick up freshly killed pigs and take them to the packing house.
He was supposed to be home by 4 am, but would usually go to bars after work.

By the early 1910s, he was playing at clubs in New York City and Atlantic City, New Jersey.
